{"title":"Trickstuff locks down Centerlock, gives brake calipers more breathing room","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/01/trickstuff-locks-down-centerlock-gives-brake-calipers-more-breathing-room/","date":1630539161000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-270164\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>If you ride Centerlock brake rotors, you fall into two camps: Those that haven’t had a problem, and those that’ve had it come loose on a ride. While there are<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/03/13/review-uniors-tiny-multi-purpose-pocket-lockring-tool-saves-the-day/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"> a couple of mini tools</a> that can <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/04/22/clever-portable-tools-from-terske-turn-your-thru-axle-into-a-crank-lockring-or-pedal-wrench/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">re-tighten a Centerlock bolt</a>, the better solution is to not let it come loose in the first place, and that’s where Trickstuff’s new product comes in…</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185235/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185235/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-1.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:740x555/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" alt=\"trickstuff Center Block adapter for 6-bolt rotors that can't come loose\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1200\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185235/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-1.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185235/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-1-297x223.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185235/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-1-800x600.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185235/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-1-120x90.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185235/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-1-768x576.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185235/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-1-1536x1152.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185235/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-1.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:740x555/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" ezoid=\"0.09621973775908166\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185235/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-1.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185235/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-1-297x223.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185235/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-1-800x600.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185235/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-1-120x90.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185235/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-1-768x576.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185235/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-1-1536x1152.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1536w\"></a></p><p>Internally called the Center Block (the name may change for production), they say it’s the first 6-bolt-to-Centerlock adapter that can’t accidentally loosen.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185239/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185239/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-2.jpg\" alt=\"trickstuff Center Block adapter for 6-bolt rotors that can't come loose\" width=\"1400\" height=\"1050\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185239/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-2.jpg 1400w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185239/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-2-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185239/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-2-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185239/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-2-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185239/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-2-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185239/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-2.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185239/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-2.jpg 1400w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185239/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-2-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185239/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-2-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185239/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-2-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185239/trickstuff-centerblock-6-bolt-to-centerlock-adapter-eurobike-2021-2-768x576.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p>The lock ring uses 8 holes in an asymmetric pattern, so once you get it tightened to the appropriate torque spec, go just a bit further then snap the C-clip in to prevent it from turning. Check the top photo to see it clipped into place, showing how the bend in the C-clip notches into the recess in the lock ring, then dropping into one of the holes below it.</p><p>MSRP will be €29, available this fall.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185221/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185221/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2.jpg\" alt=\"trickstuff c22 2-piston brake caliper for road and gravel bikes updated for 2021\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1199\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185221/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185221/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185221/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185221/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185221/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185221/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2-1536x1151.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185221/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185221/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185221/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185221/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185221/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185221/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185221/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2-1536x1151.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p>Trickstuff has updated their2-piston C22 caliper, aimed at road and gravel bikes (and XC) with a bigger pad opening gap, helping it fit more bikes better since the flat mount standard is, um, not quite standard enough. So, there’s more space to adjust it to prevent the rotor rubbing on the caliper body:</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185218/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185218/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1.jpg\" alt=\"trickstuff c22 2-piston brake caliper for road and gravel bikes updated for 2021\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1200\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185218/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185218/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185218/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185218/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185218/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185218/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185218/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185218/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185218/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185218/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185218/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185218/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185218/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p>They also gave it a refined Shimano hose attachment, making it easier to plug and play directly to that brand’s hoses. They also have SRAM versions, but we asked, why would someone want to replace a Shimano road brake caliper? They say it has more power than Shimano’s brakes, but admit that not everyone wants their brakes to be more powerful on a road bike. But if you do, here’s an option.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185225/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185225/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-3.jpg\" alt=\"trickstuff c22 2-piston brake caliper for road and gravel bikes updated for 2021\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1200\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185225/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-3.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185225/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-3-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185225/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-3-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185225/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-3-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185225/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-3-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185225/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-3-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185225/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-3.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185225/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-3.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185225/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-3-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185225/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-3-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185225/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-3-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185225/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-3-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185225/trickstuff-c22-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-3-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p>It’s also available in post-mount versions, and there’s a new bleed Port with a separate nut to close flow, so you can attach the syringe, then open the port so that it won’t leak.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185229/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185229/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1.jpg\" alt=\"trickstuff c42 4-piston disc brake calipers for mountain bikes\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1200\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185229/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185229/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185229/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185229/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185229/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185229/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185229/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185229/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185229/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185229/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185229/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185229/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185229/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-1-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p>Similar updates, including the rotor slot spacing and bleed port, come to their 4-piston C42 mountain bike caliper.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185232/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185232/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2.jpg\" alt=\"trickstuff c42 4-piston disc brake calipers for mountain bikes\" width=\"1281\" height=\"961\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185232/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2.jpg 1281w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185232/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185232/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185232/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185232/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1281px) 100vw, 1281px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185232/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185232/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2.jpg 1281w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185232/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185232/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185232/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185232/trickstuff-c42-disc-brake-caliper-eurobike-2021-2-768x576.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p>It gets a wider rotor slot to make it easier to mount on a wider variety of frames, too. These also get a new 850 pad shape that matches SRAM’s pads, so you can find replacements easier, even though they say their pad compounds are stronger.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185245/trickstuff-lightweight-sl-disc-brake-rotor-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185245/trickstuff-lightweight-sl-disc-brake-rotor-1.jpg\" alt=\"trickstuff brake rotors\" width=\"1400\" height=\"1050\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185245/trickstuff-lightweight-sl-disc-brake-rotor-1.jpg 1400w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185245/trickstuff-lightweight-sl-disc-brake-rotor-1-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185245/trickstuff-lightweight-sl-disc-brake-rotor-1-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185245/trickstuff-lightweight-sl-disc-brake-rotor-1-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185245/trickstuff-lightweight-sl-disc-brake-rotor-1-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185245/trickstuff-lightweight-sl-disc-brake-rotor-1.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185245/trickstuff-lightweight-sl-disc-brake-rotor-1.jpg 1400w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185245/trickstuff-lightweight-sl-disc-brake-rotor-1-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185245/trickstuff-lightweight-sl-disc-brake-rotor-1-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185245/trickstuff-lightweight-sl-disc-brake-rotor-1-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01185245/trickstuff-lightweight-sl-disc-brake-rotor-1-768x576.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p>Notice that brake rotor profile from the prior photo? It’s nice and bezeled to prevent it from cutting you, but it also shows off the thickness. Trickstuff’s says their brake rotors are thicker than the comptition, which helps with heat management. The smaller 140mm and 160mm are 1.85mm thick, and the 180mm and larger are&nbsp;2.05mm.</p><p>They come in two versions, the SL shown directly above, and the regular one for more aggressive riders shown at the top of this post. Claimed weights for a 180mm rotor are about 120g (SL) to 150g (regular).</p><p>They only make 6-bolt rotors at the moment, but say Centerlock rotors are on the way and will incorporate the Center Block locking design.</p><p><em><a href=\"https://trickstuff.de/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Trickstuff.de</a></em></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"54f18bfb87cd0ae3bbaffa790e2111010e9773224c1874ad46dd331ff9c1fc88","category":"Cycling"}